The paper deals with online matching algorithms, which are typically studied in the area of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses stochastic models and their analysis, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of LP benchmarks and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these algorithms to online advertising, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
